news.title: Mumbai: Dharavi residents resisting eligibility survey face warning
news.para: In a press release issued on Thursday, the NMDPL stated that so far it covered 80,000 tenements. Posters have been put up in lanes, societies, and tenements where people have been resisting the survey.

news.title: Panasonic Life Solutions India acquires 6,586.90 sq meters land in Mumbai for Rs 160 crore
news.para: The land, spanning approximately 6,586.90 sq meters (about 7,877.87 sq yards), was acquired by Panasonic Life Solutions India from River Rose Developers LLP, as per IGR property registration documents.

news.title: Blackstone in talks to buy stake in New York City office building: Sources
news.para: The planned move comes as Blackstone executives signaled on an earnings call earlier in the day that the troubled commercial real estate sector was stabilizing.

news.title: Delhi: Birla Cotton Mills to be redeveloped into residential mixed-use project
news.para: All the partners will jointly develop 30 lakh square feet of housing and retail space on this land parcel owned by Saroj Kumar Poddar-led Adventz Group firm Texmaco Infrastructure and Holdings.

news.title: Ajmera Realty acquires 1,341.1 sq meter land in Mumbai for Rs 51 crore
news.para: Ajmera Realty & Infra India acquired the land through a competitive bidding process from Karamshi Jethabhai Somaiya Trust at a cost of Rs 51 crore.

news.title: Noida: District administration reminds 200 buildings to register lifts by March 25
news.para: With the March 25 deadline not far away, the district administration recently sent them reminders to complete the procedure or pay a penalty.

news.title: Mumbai: No bids for Mhada's Kala Chowkie redevelopment, deadline extended again
news.para: Mhada officials said the authority promised residents 635-686 sqft carpet free flats, but builders indicated 508 sqft can be given.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP issues notices to owners of 650 properties in DLF-2
news.para: The notices were issued after a large-scale survey, carried out on the directions of the Punjab and Haryana high court, found widespread violation of rules in the city's upscale residential sectors.

news.title: Hyderabad: Real estate firm owner arrested for cheating villa buyers
news.para: G Vijay Lakshmi is the owner of Sri Laxmi Constructions, Laxmi Magnus Constructions, and Bhavana GLC Cribs, located in Mallampet.

news.title: HeidelbergCement India profit down 83.5% to Rs 5.19 crore in Q3 FY25
news.para: Its revenue from operations declined 10.6 per cent to Rs 542.82 crore during the December quarter. It was at Rs 607.13 crore a year ago.

news.title: Prestige Estates Projects' net profit dips 80.45% in Q3 FY25
news.para: Prestige Estates Projects' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 1,697.90 crore in Q3 FY25, a dip of 13.83 per cent from Rs 1,970.50 crore in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Residential real estate sales to grow 17% in FY25: Ind-Ra
news.para: The rating agency has maintained a neutral outlook for the residential real estate sector for FY26.

news.title: The Phoenix Mills net profit increases by 2.02% in Q3 FY25
news.para: The Phoenix Mills' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 1,005.52 crore in Q3 FY25, a dip of 1.47 per cent from Rs 1,020.48 crore in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Court denies anticipatory bail to Popular Builders' owner in land forgery case
news.para: CID (Crime) registered a complaint from one Kanu Thakor in Aug 2024, claiming that his ancestral land was illegally purchased by the accused persons using forged documents involving his grandmother in 1986 when, in fact, his grandmother died in 1980.

news.title: Kalpataru denies links to fraudulent group misusing its name
news.para: The statement from Kalpataru Ltd. rejected any connection to the alleged fraudulent activities and stated that the company's name and trademark have been unlawfully used by a separate group of individuals.

news.title: Transform your space with smart interior solutions
news.para: VOX Group is a leading European brand specializing in interior and exterior finishing solutions. With over 30+ years of experience, VOX is known for its innovation, craftsmanship, and high-quality products.

news.title: Dharwad zilla panchayat launches property tax collection campaign
news.para: Property tax is a major component of revenue for any local body and no development works can be taken up if tax revenue is not generated.

news.title: Sales of office buildings in Europe slumped to lowest since 2009 last year
news.para: The commercial real estate market globally has endured tough trading since the COVID-19 pandemic, largely driven by higher borrowing costs and changing working patterns, the latter hitting offices particularly hard.

news.title: RBI files application for insolvency proceedings against Aviom India Housing Finance
news.para: On Monday, the RBI superseded the board of Aviom India Housing Finance owing to governance concerns and defaults in meeting various payment obligations.

news.title: Shree Cement's net profit declines 72.40% in Q3 FY25
news.para: Shree Cement's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 4,683.46 crore in Q3 FY25, a dip of 12.31 per cent from Rs 5,340.94 crore in the similar quarter last year.
